A '''tensometer''' is a device used to evaluate the [[Young's modulus]] (how much it stretches under strain) of a material.  
The tensometer is usually loaded with a sample between two grips that are adjusted manually to apply [[force]] to the specimen.  The measurements taken are force and extension.  A tensometer can be either electronic or manual, the latter being operated by a handle to apply the force.

